T|Cros|0|Both vt share the same bottleneck: an infrastructure was architected but never operationalized. For nz this is a tactical gap (one ap call); for hb it's structural (pd must exist first).
T|Cros|1|SS26 is the immediate risk. A late-June cg launch w/ no pre-launch baseline means every budget decision in the first 30 days will be reactive, not data-driven. Base rate: 30-40% ROAS underperformance in first month for DTC launches w/o baselines.
T|Cros|2|ka's posture shift is ro's dependency. ka needs operational authority to trigger data collection (not just consume it). dn shd add "prime data pipelines" to the Monday checklist. Until ka can pull data, ro — and nt, and fx — are flying blind.
T|Cros|3|kh pre-mortem on SS26 shd be scheduled now — before budget is committed, not after. The "no baseline" scenario is exactly the kind of overconfidence risk kh exists to catch: "we'll figure it out as we go" is a planning fallacy dressed as agility.
